Ajinomoto Co Inc &lt;AJIN.T> said it willsign around end-April to buy the 50 pct of &lt;Knorr Foods CoLtd>, capitalised at four billion yen, that it does not alreadyown from its U.S. Partner &lt;CPC International Inc>.    Ajinomoto will also acquire 50 pct each of CPC's two salessubsidiaries and six production units in Hong Kong, thePhilippines, Singapore, Malaysia, Taiwan and Thailand, he said.    The total cost of the acquisition is 340 mln dlrs, thespokesman said. REUTER&#3;